Apache instructions for running wsgi.py with python3 venv:

1. Install mod-wsgi for python3
    1.1 apt-get install apache2-dev
    1.2 extract mod_wsgi-4.4.13.tar.gz and compile it:
        1.2.1 ./configure --with-python=/path/to/venv/bin/python3
        1.2.2 make
        1.2.3 make install
    1.3 copy wsgi.load file to apache mods-available
    1.4 create link from mods-enabled wsgi.load to mods-available.

2. Configure apache's python interpreter to the virtual env
    2.1 insert "WSGIPythonHome /path/to/pythonenv/env-name" to apache2.conf